## Why

MUI ships size snapshots per commit; **barrel imports** (`@mui/material`, `@mui/icons-material`) hurt **dev startup/rebuild** most — not only bundle size. Prefer **default path imports** (matches MUI docs/examples).

## Imports

- **Components**: `import Button from '@mui/material/Button'` — not `import { Button } from '@mui/material'`.
- **Icons**: `import Delete from '@mui/icons-material/Delete'` — not `import { Delete } from '@mui/icons-material'` (icons: path imports much faster in dev).

## Migrate barrels → paths

```bash
npx @mui/codemod@latest v5.0.0/path-imports <path>
```

## ESLint (optional guard)

`no-restricted-imports` patterns: `{ "regex": "^@mui/[^/]+$" }` — blocks package root barrels only.

## VS Code auto-import

`.vscode/settings.json`: `typescript.preferences.autoImportSpecifierExcludeRegexes`: `["^@mui/[^/]+$"]` — nudges path imports.

## Bundlers

- **Next.js ≥13.5**: `optimizePackageImports` can optimize MUI imports; still prefer path imports for consistency unless team standard says otherwise.
- **Parcel**: set `"@parcel/resolver-default": { "packageExports": true }` in `package.json` so ESM/exports resolve correctly.

## Theme overrides — gotchas

### Child themes use `mergeThemeOptions`, not raw `deepmerge`

PMM/SEP extend BaseTheme via `mergeThemeOptions` in `src/design/merge-theme-options.ts`. It deep-merges theme options and additionally:

- **composes `styleOverrides`** (object or function, at top level or per slot) instead of replacing them — child wins on conflicting keys, base slots survive.
- **concatenates `variants`** base-first so base variants survive and child variants cascade last (win on conflict).

Use `mergeThemeOptions(baseThemeOptions(mode), newOptions)` in child themes; never raw `deepmerge` for theme extension. Note other array-valued config (anything besides `variants`) is still replaced by `deepmerge`, not merged — if a new array slot needs to compose, extend `mergeThemeOptions` rather than redeclaring it in the child.

### MUI v7 drives hover backgrounds via CSS custom properties

For example, `IconButton`'s hover bg is `var(--IconButton-hoverBg)`, set per-variant. To override hover behavior, set the CSS var on the appropriate slot (e.g. `"--IconButton-hoverBg": theme.palette.action.hover` in `colorSecondary`) rather than writing `"&:hover": { backgroundColor: ... }`. Same pattern exists for other components — grep `--{Component}-` in MUI source first.
